      <div xml:id="NA144-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu āṟṟatu ētattiṟkuk kavaṉṟu ciṟaippuṟamākat talaivi (ET: ētam niṉaintu kavaṉṟa talaivi ciṟaippuṟamākac) colliyatu (ETv: coṟṟatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said, anxious because of the reason ???, while [HE] was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA144">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            peruṅkaḷi ṟuḻuvai tākkali ṉirumpiṭik</l>
<l>            karuvi māmaḻai yarava mañcum</l>
<l rend="indent4">            vāṅkamaik kaḻaiyi ṉaralum pūcaṟkup</l>
<l>            pōtē ruṇkaṇ kaliḻavu mētil</l>
<l>            pētai neñcaṅ kavalai kavaṟṟa</l>
<l>            vaṅkā kiṉṟāṟ ṟōḻi pakuvāyp </l>
<l>            piṇavuppuli vaḻaṅku maṇaṅkaruṅ kavalai</l>
<l rend="indent4">            piṇavuppaci tīriya pēḻvā yirumpuli</l>
<l rend="indent4">            piṇaṅkari loṭuṅku maṇaṅkaruṅ kavalaiya</l>
<l>            yaviraṟa loḻukum viraicelaṟ kāṉyāṟṟuk</l>
<l>            karaiyaruṅ kuṭṭan tamiyar nīnti</l>
<l>            viravumalar poṟitta tōḷa</l>
<l>            riraviṉ varuta laṟiyā tōṟkē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Thus it has become, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while my strange foolish heart causes distress</l>
<l rend="indent2">and my bud-like kajal eyes are weeping,</l>
<l rend="indent3">fearing the sound of rain great in amount<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">karuvi mā maḻai</term>: the epithets are formulaic, and the whole usually refers to rain, but here the topos rather seems to be the likeness of the elephant’s roar and thunder, so perhaps <term xml:lang="ta">maḻai</term> means the thundering cloud.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">in [the voice of] the dark elephant cow,</l>
<l rend="indent4">when the big elephant bull attacks the tiger,</l>
<l>– for the one who does not know of coming at night,</l>
<l>he with a shoulder imprinted by mixed blossoms,</l>
<l>swimming all alone in the difficult depth to the shore<note place="foot">The relation of <term xml:lang="ta">karai</term> with <term xml:lang="ta">kuṭṭam</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">yāṟṟu</term> is completely unmarked.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">of the swift-going forest river where shimmering water flows,</l>
<l rend="indent2">by crossroads difficult with torments(?)<note place="foot">Does <term xml:lang="ta">aṇaṅku</term> here refer to malevolent spirits?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">where the broad-mouthed female tiger roams.</l>
        </lg>
